  "body": "### Messages not sent always.\r\n\r\nAs a tester verifying if Status messages are sent across properly\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # Defect\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nMessages should be working between two Status apps just like Whatsapp\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nDoesn't work so. After a period of inactivity, when we try to send messages, messages are not received. The online status on phones reflects that they have been active a while ago. At the same time Whatsapp messages are being sent successfully across.\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\nScenario 1:\r\n- Open Status on Phone A and Phone B and sign in on both.\r\n- Add Phone B contact to A and send a message to B\r\n- Message received by B\r\n- Send message from Phone B to Phone A\r\n- Message received by A\r\n- After a while note that the chat windows are still open\r\n- Send message from phone A to Phone B and viceversa\r\n- Messages not sent\r\n- At the same time send whatsapp messages across \r\n- Whatsapp messages are successfully received\r\n\r\nScenario 2\r\n- Phone A not signed into Status\r\n- Phone B - Status chat window left from a while ago\r\n- Sign in to PhoneA\r\n- Send message from Phone B to Phone A\r\n- Message received successfully on PhoneA\r\n- Send message from PhoneA to PhoneB\r\n- No message is received\r\n- Sign out from Phone B and sign in again.\r\n- Message now received on Phone B from A\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n- [ ] ...\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: ...\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: <Android|iOS>\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat)\r\n```\r\n...\r\n```",
